<task id="task_vyl_plv_4t">
    <title>To Configure Security Group Settings</title>
    <shortdesc>Before launching a <keyword keyref="prodShort"/> VM instance, you must create a
        security group that  exposes only the necessary network ports (or modify an existing group
        using the following properties).</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
            <othermeta name="author" content="Michael Khmelnitsky"/>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Project</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Compute</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Access &amp; Security</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade> to see a list of the existing security groups available in your
                    account.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>+ Create Security Group</uicontrol> and enter a name and
                    description for your new security group (for example,
                        <uicontrol>Name:</uicontrol>
                    <userinput><keyword keyref="sampleSecGroup"/></userinput>,
                        <uicontrol>Description:</uicontrol>
                    <userinput>Public-facing <keyword keyref="prodShort"/>micro
                    cloud</userinput>).</cmd>
                <info>
                    <note>If you already have security group rules matching the requirements below,
                        skip this step and launch a <keyword keyref="prodShort"/> VM
                        instance.</note>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Manage Rules</uicontrol> for the new security group.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <note>By default, a new group has open egress rules. Do not modify these rules
                        unless you have special security requirements forbidding this, because
                            <keyword keyref="prodShort"/> requires access to several remote domains
                        for updates and package management.</note>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>+ Add Rule</uicontrol> and enter the following new ingress
                    rules:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_i3t_dqv_4t">
                        <tgroup cols="3">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Rule</entry>
                                    <entry>Remote</entry>
                                    <entry>CIDR</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>HTTP</entry>
                                    <entry>CIDR</entry>
                                    <entry><uicontrol>0.0.0.0/0</uicontrol></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>HTTPS</entry>
                                    <entry>CIDR</entry>
                                    <entry><uicontrol>0.0.0.0/0</uicontrol></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>SSH</entry>
                                    <entry>CIDR</entry>
                                    <entry><uicontrol>0.0.0.0/0</uicontrol></entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>(Optional) If you require a stricter set of rules (for example, restricting SSH
                    access to a specific IP range), modify the rules above to suit your needs.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <note type="tip">For more information on the ports required by services, see
                            <b>Port Configuration</b>.</note>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
